title: For Sale:  Custom Star Model B Super 9mm
postcontent: Say "What" Again!  - Samuel Jackson, Pulp Fiction, while holding his Star Model B.Awesome “1911 style” 9mm handgun, built with a quality of craftsmanship you just do not see anymore. The “Super” resembles the 1911 in appearance yet incorporates the locking mechanism of the FN Hi Power. It was used as a stand-in for 1911s in many movies.In 1946 Star introduced the Pistola Modelo B Super in 9mm Parabellum. This design replaced the barrel link with a cam similar to that used on the FN Hi-Power pistol and had a quick takedown system that allowed the slide unit to be removed en bloc. The extractor was modified to act as a loaded-chamber indicator, and a magazine disconnect safety was also included in the design. The Modelo B Super was the first 9mm Parabellum pistol to be taken into service with the Spanish armed forces. It was the “standard” issue pistol of the Spanish Army and Guardia Civil. From the 1950s through 1975, the Spanish Army and La Legion Extranjera (the Spanish Foreign Legion) engaged in a series of campaigns against nationalist guerillas in her African colonies. The Modelo B Super saw wide service during the fighting in Spanish Morocco, Ifni and the Spanish Sahara.Pistol is in great shape and includes one 8-round magazine.  Check my other listings for a pair of NEW Galco COmbat Master holsters that fit the Star B Super perfectly.Buyer must have a CWP or be willing to transfer the firearm via a FFL.
